It is possible to run any task in any sub-project from the top (or any other subproject), by using the format :SUBPROJECT:TASK as the task name. 
This removes the need to do the following alternative (which also works):

If you were to spend a lot of time working in one sub-project, changing to that directory and running the build from there is normal. 
    However, if you need to quickly run a task in a specific subproject, 
    having the flexibility to specify the task by subproject path is very helpful.

* Include the documentation in the distribution archive

* Refactor common build script code
    